# BERT Training on Twitter Sentiment Dataset with PyQt GUI 
## 1. Introduction This project is based on Twitter sentiment analysis using a trained BERT model. The purpose of the system is to classify tweets or manually typed sentences as Positive or Negative. A PyQt desktop GUI was developed to connect the trained model with a user-friendly interface. 
## 2. Dataset Description The dataset used in this project is a Twitter sentiment dataset. It contains tweet text and polarity labels. The original polarity values were converted into binary sentiment labels. Polarity 0 was mapped as Negative and polarity 4 was mapped as Positive. A balanced dataset was created by selecting an equal number of positive and negative tweets. 
